snippet.textDisplay:
@Aison One doesn't have to be a CCP supporter to understand that all those complaints and grievances are a fiction of imagination, and they carried malicious intents. Put it simply, China is not unknown to put its best foot forward. It is propaganda. All nations do it, and China is not immune to this. And can anyone imagine that China spent all those $Billions to impress the world, and will skim on a few $Millions on food? Surely it doesn't make sense.

As for the accusation of cheating. I watched the replays, not so much the race itself as I know nothing about speed skating. However, I watched closely the referee who scanned the video replays. He clearly wasn't a Chinese referee. I bet he is an "accredited" Olympics referee. To be accredited, he/she must demonstrate the utmost fairness, accuracy, and above all, integrity. Why? Because his reputation, both personal and professional, will be tarnished forever for being corrupt. Sure, he/she could make mistakes, but I doubt it would be intentional for the reasons I listed.

I wonder what is wrong with the Koreans? A small number of American bitched and moaned about the food and the accommodation and facilities. That could be expected as they are Americans, and they are patriotic. But Koreans? And above all, they believed that their food is so much better than Chinese food? That is a big stretch. So the Olympics is now a food competition as well? Ridiculous and frivolous to the extreme. Just give them some cabbages and salt, and they could make their own Kinchi.

The Beijing Winter Olympics will provide 678 kinds of food, including food from all over the world, It may be the Olympics with the most abundant food, All kinds of services including food are free, I watch videos of many athletes. They are generally satisfied with the evaluation of food,What is a fact that is easy to verify......the South Korean speed skating team was punished by the Olympic Committee for a foul, the appeal was dismissed,That's why there's so much resentment，If you pay attention to sports, you may know South Korea's malicious fouls have long been notorious in the sports world,Especially speed skating project ...
